<subSubSection pageId="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,474,1111]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1014,1039]" pageId="7">Remarks</emphasis>
. This mite was collected from leaf blisters. Based on the large range of host plant species documented, a careful examination of 
<taxonomicName box="[588,665,1051,1074]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Eriophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyri">
<emphasis box="[588,665,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="7">E. pyri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations recorded on different plant hosts should be carried out, combining morphometric studies with biological and molecular data.
</paragraph>
